cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SI, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the security and privacy threats posed by the communication channels between browser extensions and web applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses proposals and countermeasures, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper analyzes the communication interfaces exposed by browser extensions, which could also place it in cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the impact on browsers and users, which could place it in cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
